{
  "video_id": "6ORDQFh0Byw",
  "title": "Lesley Hazleton: The doubt essential to faith",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12496.0,
      "end_time": 18216.0,
      "text": "Writing biography is a strange thing to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18216.0,
      "end_time": 20899.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a journey into the foreign territory"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 20899.0,
      "end_time": 24950.0,
      "text": "of somebody else&#39;s life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24950.0,
      "end_time": 26768.0,
      "text": "a journey, an exploration that can take you places"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 26768.0,
      "end_time": 29390.0,
      "text": "you never dreamed of going"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29390.0,
      "end_time": 31264.0,
      "text": "and still can&#39;t quite believe you&#39;ve been,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 31264.0,
      "end_time": 34992.0,
      "text": "especially if, like me, you&#39;re an agnostic Jew"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 34992.0,
      "end_time": 36817.0,
      "text": "and the life you&#39;ve been exploring"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36817.0,
      "end_time": 41649.0,
      "text": "is that of Muhammad."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 41649.0,
      "end_time": 44800.0,
      "text": "Five years ago, for instance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44800.0,
      "end_time": 47348.0,
      "text": "I found myself waking each morning in misty Seattle"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47348.0,
      "end_time": 50830.0,
      "text": "to what I knew was an impossible question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50831.0,
      "end_time": 54490.0,
      "text": "What actually happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 54490.0,
      "end_time": 55488.0,
      "text": "one desert night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55488.0,
      "end_time": 59820.0,
      "text": "half the world and almost half of history away?"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59820.0,
      "end_time": 60802.0,
      "text": "What happened, that is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60802.0,
      "end_time": 63120.0,
      "text": "on the night in the year 610"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63120.0,
      "end_time": 66971.0,
      "text": "when Muhammad received the first revelation of the Koran"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 66971.0,
      "end_time": 71480.0,
      "text": "on a mountain just outside Mecca?"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 71480.0,
      "end_time": 75653.0,
      "text": "This is the core mystical moment of Islam,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75653.0,
      "end_time": 77190.0,
      "text": "and as such, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 77190.0,
      "end_time": 80950.0,
      "text": "it defies empirical analysis."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80950.0,
      "end_time": 84200.0,
      "text": "Yet the question wouldn&#39;t let go of me."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 84200.0,
      "end_time": 87384.0,
      "text": "I was fully aware that for someone as secular as I am,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87384.0,
      "end_time": 89263.0,
      "text": "just asking it could be seen"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89263.0,
      "end_time": 92523.0,
      "text": "as pure chutzpah."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 92523.0,
      "end_time": 95205.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 95205.0,
      "end_time": 97816.0,
      "text": "And I plead guilty as charged,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 97816.0,
      "end_time": 101847.0,
      "text": "because all exploration, physical or intellectual,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 101847.0,
      "end_time": 105723.0,
      "text": "is inevitably in some sense an act of transgression,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 105724.0,
      "end_time": 109121.0,
      "text": "of crossing boundaries."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 109121.0,
      "end_time": 115136.0,
      "text": "Still, some boundaries are larger than others."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 115136.0,
      "end_time": 118560.0,
      "text": "So a human encountering the divine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 118560.0,
      "end_time": 121178.0,
      "text": "as Muslims believe Muhammad did,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 121178.0,
      "end_time": 124180.0,
      "text": "to the rationalist, this is a matter not of fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 124190.0,
      "end_time": 125776.0,
      "text": "but of wishful fiction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125776.0,
      "end_time": 129714.0,
      "text": "and like all of us, I like to think of myself as rational."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 129714.0,
      "end_time": 132597.0,
      "text": "Which might be why when I looked at the earliest accounts"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 132598.0,
      "end_time": 134375.0,
      "text": "we have of that night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 134375.0,
      "end_time": 137194.0,
      "text": "what struck me even more than what happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137194.0,
      "end_time": 142715.0,
      "text": "was what did not happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 142716.0,
      "end_time": 145868.0,
      "text": "Muhammad did not come floating off the mountain"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 145868.0,
      "end_time": 148817.0,
      "text": "as though walking on air."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 148818.0,
      "end_time": 151292.0,
      "text": "He did not run down shouting, \"Hallelujah!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 151292.0,
      "end_time": 153652.0,
      "text": "and \"Bless the Lord!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 153652.0,
      "end_time": 157380.0,
      "text": "He did not radiate light and joy."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 157380.0,
      "end_time": 158959.0,
      "text": "There were no choirs of angels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 158959.0,
      "end_time": 162259.0,
      "text": "no music of the spheres, no elation, no ecstasy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162259.0,
      "end_time": 165921.0,
      "text": "no golden aura surrounding him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 165921.0,
      "end_time": 170630.0,
      "text": "no sense of an absolute, fore-ordained role"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 170630.0,
      "end_time": 173138.0,
      "text": "as the messenger of God."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 173139.0,
      "end_time": 176940.0,
      "text": "That is, he did none of the things"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 176940.0,
      "end_time": 178847.0,
      "text": "that might make it easy to cry foul,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 178848.0,
      "end_time": 183995.0,
      "text": "to put down the whole story as a pious fable."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 183995.0,
      "end_time": 186827.0,
      "text": "Quite the contrary."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 186827.0,
      "end_time": 190572.0,
      "text": "In his own reported words,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 190572.0,
      "end_time": 192949.0,
      "text": "he was convinced at first"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 192949.0,
      "end_time": 198230.0,
      "text": "that what had happened couldn&#39;t have been real."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 198230.0,
      "end_time": 200941.0,
      "text": "At best, he thought, it had to have been a hallucination --"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 200942.0,
      "end_time": 202751.0,
      "text": "a trick of the eye or the ear, perhaps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 202751.0,
      "end_time": 204926.0,
      "text": "or his own mind working against him."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 204926.0,
      "end_time": 207102.0,
      "text": "At worst, possession --"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 207103.0,
      "end_time": 209392.0,
      "text": "that he&#39;d been seized by an evil jinn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 209392.0,
      "end_time": 211183.0,
      "text": "a spirit out to deceive him,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 211183.0,
      "end_time": 214191.0,
      "text": "even to crush the life out of him."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 214192.0,
      "end_time": 217216.0,
      "text": "In fact, he was so sure that he could only be majnun,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 217216.0,
      "end_time": 218844.0,
      "text": "possessed by a jinn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 218844.0,
      "end_time": 220956.0,
      "text": "that when he found himself still alive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 220956.0,
      "end_time": 225804.0,
      "text": "his first impulse was to finish the job himself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 225805.0,
      "end_time": 228800.0,
      "text": "to leap off the highest cliff"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 228800.0,
      "end_time": 232126.0,
      "text": "and escape the terror of what he&#39;d experienced"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 232126.0,
      "end_time": 239228.0,
      "text": "by putting an end to all experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 239228.0,
      "end_time": 242148.0,
      "text": "So the man who fled down the mountain that night"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 242148.0,
      "end_time": 244599.0,
      "text": "trembled not with joy"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 244599.0,
      "end_time": 249319.0,
      "text": "but with a stark, primordial fear."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 249319.0,
      "end_time": 255238.0,
      "text": "He was overwhelmed not with conviction, but by doubt."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 255239.0,
      "end_time": 258400.0,
      "text": "And that panicked disorientation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 258399.99999999997,
      "end_time": 260918.99999999997,
      "text": "that sundering of everything familiar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 260918.0,
      "end_time": 264587.0,
      "text": "that daunting awareness of something"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 264603.0,
      "end_time": 267512.0,
      "text": "beyond human comprehension,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 267512.0,
      "end_time": 274870.0,
      "text": "can only be called a terrible awe."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 274870.0,
      "end_time": 277301.0,
      "text": "This might be somewhat difficult to grasp"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 277301.0,
      "end_time": 279839.0,
      "text": "now that we use the word \"awesome\""
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 279839.0,
      "end_time": 284180.0,
      "text": "to describe a new app or a viral video."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 284180.0,
      "end_time": 287222.0,
      "text": "With the exception perhaps of a massive earthquake,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 287223.0,
      "end_time": 289871.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re protected from real awe."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 289871.0,
      "end_time": 291758.0,
      "text": "We close the doors and hunker down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 291759.0,
      "end_time": 294305.0,
      "text": "convinced that we&#39;re in control,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 294305.0,
      "end_time": 297327.0,
      "text": "or, at least, hoping for control."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 297327.0,
      "end_time": 299235.0,
      "text": "We do our best to ignore the fact that"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 299235.0,
      "end_time": 301296.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t always have it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 301296.0,
      "end_time": 304530.0,
      "text": "and that not everything can be explained."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 304530.0,
      "end_time": 308215.0,
      "text": "Yet whether you&#39;re a rationalist or a mystic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 308215.0,
      "end_time": 310909.0,
      "text": "whether you think the words Muhammad heard that night"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 310910.0,
      "end_time": 315174.0,
      "text": "came from inside himself or from outside,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 315174.0,
      "end_time": 319878.0,
      "text": "what&#39;s clear is that he did experience them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 319878.0,
      "end_time": 322313.0,
      "text": "and that he did so with a force that would shatter"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 322314.0,
      "end_time": 324635.0,
      "text": "his sense of himself and his world"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 324635.0,
      "end_time": 327775.0,
      "text": "and transform this otherwise modest man"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 327775.0,
      "end_time": 334467.0,
      "text": "into a radical advocate for social and economic justice."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 334468.0,
      "end_time": 339710.0,
      "text": "Fear was the only sane response,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 339710.0,
      "end_time": 344734.0,
      "text": "the only human response."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 344734.0,
      "end_time": 347241.0,
      "text": "Too human for some,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 347242.0,
      "end_time": 349975.0,
      "text": "like conservative Muslim theologians who maintain that"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 349975.0,
      "end_time": 351842.0,
      "text": "the account of his wanting to kill himself"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 351842.0,
      "end_time": 354280.0,
      "text": "shouldn&#39;t even be mentioned, despite the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 354280.0,
      "end_time": 358734.0,
      "text": "that it&#39;s in the earliest Islamic biographies."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 358734.0,
      "end_time": 361525.0,
      "text": "They insist that he never doubted"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 361525.0,
      "end_time": 368135.0,
      "text": "for even a single moment, let alone despaired."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 368135.0,
      "end_time": 371972.0,
      "text": "Demanding perfection, they refuse to tolerate"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 371972.0,
      "end_time": 376691.0,
      "text": "human imperfection."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 376691.0,
      "end_time": 383885.0,
      "text": "Yet what, exactly, is imperfect about doubt?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 383886.0,
      "end_time": 386860.0,
      "text": "As I read those early accounts, I realized it was"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 386860.0,
      "end_time": 390670.0,
      "text": "precisely Muhammad&#39;s doubt that brought him alive for me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 390670.0,
      "end_time": 393670.0,
      "text": "that allowed me to begin to see him in full,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 393670.0,
      "end_time": 396653.0,
      "text": "to accord him the integrity of reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 396653.0,
      "end_time": 398822.0,
      "text": "And the more I thought about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 398822.0,
      "end_time": 401839.0,
      "text": "the more it made sense that he doubted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 401839.0,
      "end_time": 408422.0,
      "text": "because doubt is essential to faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 408422.0,
      "end_time": 411302.0,
      "text": "If this seems a startling idea at first,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 411302.0,
      "end_time": 414963.0,
      "text": "consider that doubt, as Graham Greene once put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 414963.0,
      "end_time": 418798.0,
      "text": "is the heart of the matter."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 418798.0,
      "end_time": 423203.0,
      "text": "Abolish all doubt, and what&#39;s left is not faith,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 423203.0,
      "end_time": 428445.0,
      "text": "but absolute, heartless conviction."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 428446.0,
      "end_time": 432317.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re certain that you possess the Truth --"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 432317.0,
      "end_time": 436608.0,
      "text": "inevitably offered with an implied uppercase T --"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 436608.0,
      "end_time": 439166.0,
      "text": "and this certainty quickly devolves"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 439166.0,
      "end_time": 442678.0,
      "text": "into dogmatism and righteousness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 442678.0,
      "end_time": 446781.0,
      "text": "by which I mean a demonstrative, overweening pride"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 446781.0,
      "end_time": 450569.0,
      "text": "in being so very right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 450569.0,
      "end_time": 458457.0,
      "text": "in short, the arrogance of fundamentalism."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 458457.0,
      "end_time": 462933.0,
      "text": "It has to be one of the multiple ironies of history"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 462933.0,
      "end_time": 465991.0,
      "text": "that a favorite expletive of Muslim fundamentalists"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 465991.0,
      "end_time": 469181.0,
      "text": "is the same one once used by the Christian fundamentalists"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 469182.0,
      "end_time": 471994.0,
      "text": "known as Crusaders:"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 471994.0,
      "end_time": 477219.0,
      "text": "\"infidel,\" from the Latin for \"faithless.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 477219.0,
      "end_time": 481558.0,
      "text": "Doubly ironic, in this case, because their absolutism"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 481558.0,
      "end_time": 486220.0,
      "text": "is in fact the opposite of faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 486230.0,
      "end_time": 491982.0,
      "text": "In effect, they are the infidels."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 491982.0,
      "end_time": 494809.0,
      "text": "Like fundamentalists of all religious stripes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 494809.0,
      "end_time": 498654.0,
      "text": "they have no questions, only answers."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 498654.0,
      "end_time": 501445.0,
      "text": "They found the perfect antidote to thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 501446.0,
      "end_time": 505217.0,
      "text": "and the ideal refuge of the hard demands of real faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 505217.0,
      "end_time": 507166.0,
      "text": "They don&#39;t have to struggle for it like Jacob"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 507166.0,
      "end_time": 509216.0,
      "text": "wrestling through the night with the angel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 509216.0,
      "end_time": 512374.0,
      "text": "or like Jesus in his 40 days and nights in the wilderness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 512374.0,
      "end_time": 515576.0,
      "text": "or like Muhammad, not only that night on the mountain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 515576.0,
      "end_time": 518700.0,
      "text": "but throughout his years as a prophet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 518700.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522254.00000000006,
      "text": "with the Koran constantly urging him not to despair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 522254.0,
      "end_time": 525542.0,
      "text": "and condemning those who most loudly proclaim"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 525542.0,
      "end_time": 529339.0,
      "text": "that they know everything there is to know"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 529339.0,
      "end_time": 536233.0,
      "text": "and that they and they alone are right."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 536233.0,
      "end_time": 543646.0,
      "text": "And yet we, the vast and still far too silent majority,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 543646.0,
      "end_time": 549415.0,
      "text": "have ceded the public arena to this extremist minority."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 549415.0,
      "end_time": 551908.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve allowed Judaism to be claimed"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 551908.0,
      "end_time": 555779.0,
      "text": "by violently messianic West Bank settlers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 555779.0,
      "end_time": 558726.0,
      "text": "Christianity by homophobic hypocrites"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 558726.0,
      "end_time": 561246.0,
      "text": "and misogynistic bigots,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 561246.0,
      "end_time": 566204.0,
      "text": "Islam by suicide bombers."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 566205.0,
      "end_time": 568976.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;ve allowed ourselves to be blinded to the fact that"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 568976.0,
      "end_time": 571168.0,
      "text": "no matter whether they claim to be Christians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 571168.0,
      "end_time": 572783.0,
      "text": "Jews or Muslims,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 572783.0,
      "end_time": 578438.0,
      "text": "militant extremists are none of the above."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 578438.0,
      "end_time": 584520.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re a cult all their own, blood brothers"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 584520.0,
      "end_time": 589546.0,
      "text": "steeped in other people&#39;s blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 589546.0,
      "end_time": 591748.0,
      "text": "This isn&#39;t faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 591748.0,
      "end_time": 596910.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s fanaticism, and we have to stop confusing the two."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 596910.0,
      "end_time": 601932.0,
      "text": "We have to recognize that real faith has no easy answers."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 601932.0,
      "end_time": 606100.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s difficult and stubborn."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 606100.0,
      "end_time": 608248.0,
      "text": "It involves an ongoing struggle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 608248.0,
      "end_time": 611302.0,
      "text": "a continual questioning of what we think we know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 611302.0,
      "end_time": 613867.0,
      "text": "a wrestling with issues and ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 613867.0,
      "end_time": 617166.0,
      "text": "It goes hand in hand with doubt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 617167.0,
      "end_time": 620244.0,
      "text": "in a never-ending conversation with it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 620244.0,
      "end_time": 626639.0,
      "text": "and sometimes in conscious defiance of it."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 626639.0,
      "end_time": 631687.0,
      "text": "And this conscious defiance is why I, as an agnostic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 631687.0,
      "end_time": 635828.0,
      "text": "can still have faith."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 635828.0,
      "end_time": 638816.0,
      "text": "I have faith, for instance, that peace in the Middle East"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 638816.0,
      "end_time": 643126.0,
      "text": "is possible despite the ever-accumulating mass of evidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 643126.0,
      "end_time": 646286.0,
      "text": "to the contrary."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 646287.0,
      "end_time": 648659.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not convinced of this."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 648659.0,
      "end_time": 650783.0,
      "text": "I can hardly say I believe it."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 650783.0,
      "end_time": 652725.0,
      "text": "I can only have faith in it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 652725.0,
      "end_time": 656743.0,
      "text": "commit myself, that is, to the idea of it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 656743.0,
      "end_time": 659744.0,
      "text": "and I do this precisely because of the temptation"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 659744.0,
      "end_time": 661744.0,
      "text": "to throw up my hands in resignation"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 661744.0,
      "end_time": 665265.0,
      "text": "and retreat into silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 665265.0,
      "end_time": 669946.0,
      "text": "Because despair is self-fulfilling."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 669946.0,
      "end_time": 672266.0,
      "text": "If we call something impossible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 672266.0,
      "end_time": 676340.0,
      "text": "we act in such a way that we make it so."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 676340.0,
      "end_time": 681967.0,
      "text": "And I, for one, refuse to live that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 681967.0,
      "end_time": 684266.0,
      "text": "In fact, most of us do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 684266.0,
      "end_time": 687842.0,
      "text": "whether we&#39;re atheist or theist"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 687842.0,
      "end_time": 691782.0,
      "text": "or anywhere in between or beyond, for that matter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 691782.0,
      "end_time": 696980.0,
      "text": "what drives us is that, despite our doubts"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 696980.0,
      "end_time": 698425.0,
      "text": "and even because of our doubts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 698426.0,
      "end_time": 702898.0,
      "text": "we reject the nihilism of despair."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 702898.0,
      "end_time": 706131.0,
      "text": "We insist on faith in the future"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 706131.0,
      "end_time": 710869.0,
      "text": "and in each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 710869.0,
      "end_time": 714370.0,
      "text": "Call this naive if you like."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 714370.0,
      "end_time": 717467.0,
      "text": "Call it impossibly idealistic if you must."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 717467.0,
      "end_time": 719895.0,
      "text": "But one thing is sure:"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 719895.0,
      "end_time": 723361.0,
      "text": "Call it human."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 723361.0,
      "end_time": 726396.0,
      "text": "Could Muhammad have so radically changed his world"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 726396.0,
      "end_time": 729247.0,
      "text": "without such faith, without the refusal"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 729248.0,
      "end_time": 733964.0,
      "text": "to cede to the arrogance of closed-minded certainty?"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 733964.0,
      "end_time": 737230.0,
      "text": "I think not."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 737230.0,
      "end_time": 739273.0,
      "text": "After keeping company with him as a writer"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 739273.0,
      "end_time": 742573.0,
      "text": "for the past five years, I can&#39;t see"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 742573.0,
      "end_time": 747675.0,
      "text": "that he&#39;d be anything but utterly outraged"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 747676.0,
      "end_time": 750823.0,
      "text": "at the militant fundamentalists who claim to speak"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 750823.0,
      "end_time": 756292.0,
      "text": "and act in his name in the Middle East and elsewhere today."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 756292.0,
      "end_time": 760582.0,
      "text": "He&#39;d be appalled at the repression of half the population"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 760582.0,
      "end_time": 763580.0,
      "text": "because of their gender."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 763580.0,
      "end_time": 771561.0,
      "text": "He&#39;d be torn apart by the bitter divisiveness of sectarianism."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 771561.0,
      "end_time": 774267.0,
      "text": "He&#39;d call out terrorism for what it is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 774267.0,
      "end_time": 779110.0,
      "text": "not only criminal but an obscene travesty"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 779110.0,
      "end_time": 783915.0,
      "text": "of everything he believed in and struggled for."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 783916.0,
      "end_time": 789185.0,
      "text": "He&#39;d say what the Koran says: Anyone who takes a life"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 789185.0,
      "end_time": 792386.0,
      "text": "takes the life of all humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 792386.0,
      "end_time": 799582.0,
      "text": "Anyone who saves a life, saves the life of all humanity."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 799582.0,
      "end_time": 802652.0,
      "text": "And he&#39;d commit himself fully"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 802652.0,
      "end_time": 809672.0,
      "text": "to the hard and thorny process of making peace."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 809672.0,
      "end_time": 811107.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 811107.0,
      "end_time": 815506.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 815506.0,
      "end_time": 819506.0,
      "text": "Thank you. (Applause)"
    }
  ]
}